  "response": "Here's the difference:\n\nTortilla chips are:\n- Plain, crispy corn or flour tortilla triangles\n- Usually served as a snack or accompaniment to salsa or dips\n- Typically unseasoned and not covered with toppings\n\nNachos are:\n- Tortilla chips topped with various ingredients\n- Usually include melted cheese, and often additional toppings like:\n  - Jalape\u00f1os\n  - Sour cream\n  - Salsa\n  - Meat (ground beef, chicken)\n  - Beans\n- Served as a more substantial dish or appetizer\n- Can be prepared hot and loaded with multiple toppings\n\nSo tortilla chips are the base chip, while nachos are a prepared dish using those chips as a foundation.",
